    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix timespec normalization in protocol timer calculations\n\n### Summary\nThe protocol timer calculations in the 5G NR stack use timespec structures for high-precision timing. Several functions that add timespec values had an off-by-one error in their normalization logic. When the nanosecond component was exactly 1,000,000,000 (i.e. exactly 1 second), the functions failed to normalize it to 1 second + 0 nanoseconds, causing timing inaccuracies and potential hangs during subframe processing.\n\nThe issue manifests as intermittent timeouts during PNF/VNF synchronization, particularly under heavy load when timing calculations accumulate small errors. Affected systems may experience delayed or missed subframe indications, leading to UE connection drops and gNB restarts.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/pnf/src/pnf_p7.c`: Fixed `pnf_timespec_add` normalization condition\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/vnf/src/vnf_p7_interface.c`: Fixed `timespec_add` normalization condition  \n- `common/utils/T/tracer/view/time.c`: Fixed `time_add` normalization condition\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/view/ticktime.c`: Fixed `time_add` normalization condition\n\n"
}